caption: everything is delicious, been coming here for 6 years. Tandoori Mix grill with chickpeas and mango Lassi hits the spot

We had lamb vindaloo and chicken tikka + naan and roti, of course.  Food is solid, and we enjoyed it.  The service was what stuck out.  Very nice, tried hard to make sure our experience was pleasant.  We sat around for 2 hours drinking beer because they were so nice.

Recently ordered the Murgh Tikka Masala and Gosht Vindaloo as a pick up order (we live nearby and are trying different places in the neighborhood). The spices were on point, generous portions, and the naan was divine. When we arrived to grab our order, the staff were incredibly friendly—suffice it to say, we’ll be returning soon for more! Highly recommend if you’re looking for some warm comfort food in this cold weather!
Exquisitely authentic Indian food with the most personally attentive staff. Must try in DC.
This place provides awesome service as well as delicious menu. The best place in the city. The meals served rapidly and the rates are fair. I recommend this place.

Couldn't believe we've never been before. We have found our favorite spot. The service and food could not be better. Our jaws dropped when we got our entrees. Try the jhinga shahi and Rogan josh. UNBELIEVABLE! Covid safe!!! Great staff!

This was phenomenal food! My partner and I happened upon this place, not knowing where to eat on a snowy Wednesday evening. It was absolutely fantastic! We got two entrees and an appetizer - enough food for dinner and a lunch the next day for two people. We live locally and will absolutely be going back. I do not post reviews often, but definitely want to call out credit where it is due!

I've been here twice in the last two weeks. Everything is delicious and wonderfully spiced. My go-to is the (lamb) gosht masala and the naan is divine. I'm also crazy about the tamarind sauce so they gave me extra to take home with my leftovers. The service is excellent. On the COVID front, they are very careful and serve water in plastic bottles now. It's easy to social distance and not crowded at all.

A great place for Indian food in Woodley Park! They have a huge, colorful patio, gorgeous interior, and great food. The portions are huge and they use fresh whole spices! The owner is a lovely Indian man who is very friendly.

If I could give 6 stars, I would! The staff are friendly, the food is delicious and the outdoor seating was lit and Covid-safe. Thank you to the staff for a lovely dining experience :) we will be back!

I've eaten Indian food all over the world.  I had a similar experience as some others.  On the positive side, the naan was cooked to order and the flavor of the seasoning on the meat was very good (and spicier than typical Indian restaurants in the US).  That's why I didn't give this restaurant one star.  But, my food came with a fly on it and it definitely was not cooked freshly.  The meat was served within minutes, and upon asking if it's fresh, I was told, "Try it.  It was cooked today."  (Naturally I'm thinking WHEN today.)  The meat was warm (not hot) and dry as if it was sitting around for a long while and rewarmed.  This restaurant could be good, but it needs to have a bit more pride than to serve old / pre-cooked food if it has a chance to turn itself around.

However, despite telling us clearly that we did not want anything, he brought us two more Diet Cokes. At first we were so surprised that we did not say anything. I would not visit this restaurant again.  (Original) Wir besuchten dieses Lokal am 11.08.2016 gegen 21 Uhr Ortszeit. Für diese Uhrzeit war das Lokal sehr gering Besucht. Schon da bemerkten wir den strengen Geruch. Es roch wie auf der Katzenstation des örtlichen Katzenvereins. Nichts gegen Katzen, aber der Geruch gehört definitiv nicht in ein Restaurant!!! Leider entschieden wir uns zu bleiben. Da uns auch schnell die Karten gebracht worden sind und meine Familienmitglieder meinten, dass es zu spät sei um zu gehen.  Die Karte war ganz in Ordnung. Es gab eine große Auswahl an Indischen Speisen. Als dann der Kellner kam um unsere Bestellung aufzunehmen gab es die ersten Probleme bei der Verständigung. Eigentlich müsste man meinen, dass in America jeder der da Lebt Englisch sprechen kann. Dies war bei dem Kellner leider nicht der Fall. Man verstand ihn nur schwer bis überhaupt nicht.  Noch dazu machte er einen sehr unsympathischen eindruck der sich noch im Verlaufe unseres Besuches verfestigen sollte. Das Essen  kam dann nach einiger Zeit und es schmeckte ganz in Ordnung, Nicht sonderlich gut aber essbar. Als der Kellner nach einiger Zeit nach uns sah und uns in seiner unsympathischen Art fragte ob wir noch was Trinken wollten, gaben wir deutlich zu verstehen, dass wir nichts mehr wollten. Jedoch brachte er uns trotz klarer Aussage, dass wir nichts mehr wollten, zwei weitere Diet Cokes. Wir waren im ersten Moment so überrascht, dass wir nichts sagten. Wir dachten, vielleicht würde sie netterweise aufs Haus gehen. Leider war dies nicht so und unsere Rechnung war um Fünf Doller teurer geworden. Beim Bezahlen der Rechnung guckte uns der Kellner aus einer kleinen Entfernung mit einem Vorwurfsvollem Blick dabei zu wie wir die Rechnung betrachteten und das Geld in die schale legten. Er nahm dann Wortlos die Rechnung mit und wir gingen. Ich würde dieses Restaurant nicht noch einmal aufsuchen.

If I could give it a zero star I would. We went for a lunch buffet, the food was not bad (only OK), although it was cold. We paid for it and left (we were on a trip in DC). After 2 days I noticed that he had charged us for more than the amount that I had paid and signed for in the receipt. I contacted and confronted him about this....BE WARE!!! ...........They change the amount and take whatever amount of tip they want for themselves!!.......This is the first time I have seen such a thing!! ...... This is UNACCEPTABLE!!

Delicious. Food made with love served by funny, kind people. The people who wrote a bad review probably came on a bad night or never worked in a busy restaurant before. This place is AMAZING. We came during the summertime and sat on the patio. I ordered the same thing I always do when our waiter (who knows what good food is all about) suggested a different combination. Curious, I agreed and we got some samosas and garlic naan to match it.  Every dish was 5 stars. From the samosas to the lentils, aloo gobi and rice. They had flavor, texture, and spice that was spot on. The waitress made sure our glasses were never empty and our other waiter was the coolest guy you will ever meet. We had ras malai at the end (PSA: if you haven't tried it yet, you're seriously missing out. It is amazing.  In short, this place makes you feel happy, welcome, and leaves you with a full stomach for great prices. Overall five stars. Truly a DC gem.
